<html
  xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
  xml:lang="en"
  lang="en"
  metal:use-macro="context/@@main_template/master"
  i18n:domain="launchpad">

<body>

<metal:leftportlets fill-slot="portlets_one">
  <div tal:replace="structure context/@@+portlet-subscribers" />
</metal:leftportlets>

<metal:rightportlets fill-slot="portlets_two">
  <div tal:replace="structure context/@@+portlet-details" />
  <div tal:replace="structure context/@@+portlet-bugs" />
</metal:rightportlets>

<div metal:fill-slot="main">
  <div metal:use-macro="context/@@launchpad_form/form">

    <h1 i18n:translate=""
        metal:fill-slot="heading">Link support request to a bug report</h1>

    <div metal:fill-slot="extra_info">
      <p i18n:translate="">Enter the number or nickname of the Malone bug report
        that should be linked to ticket #<tal:id i18n:name="id" replace="context/id" />
        &ldquo;<tal:title i18n:name="title" replace="context/title"/>&rdquo;.
      </p>

      <p i18n:translate="">If you don't know the bug number, you can search for it
        on the <a href=""
                  tal:attributes="href string:${context/target/fmt:url}/+bugs"
                  >Bugs Listing</a> page.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<metal:help fill-slot="help">
  <p>You can link a bug to a support request. You
    should do this, if the problem described in the support request is related
    to a bug already filed. The link to the bug report will appear on the
    support request page, and a link to the support request will appear on
    the target bug page.
  </p>
  <p>You need to know the bug number that you want to link to. You will
    probably want to use the search page to locate the bug, if you don't
    know its ID.
  </p>
</metal:help>
</body>
</html>

